X-ray absorption coefficient: The absorption coefficient (α) is the efficiency of a scintillator to absorb the incident X-ray photon energy in the conversion stage, which can be expressed by the following equation [1]:1α=ρZ4/AE3\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
